Lets go to Heathrow and sneak some guns through the metal detector bay....come fly with me.....lets fly ....lets fly away they say....<br>
<br>
Yes, here we go again...<br>
<br>
The first incident was under a month ago, and was reported by the Daily Record. They got one of their journalists to fly in the name of a 11th September Hijacker from London Luton to Glasgow...as well as from Edinburgh to London Stansted...<br>
<br>
He went to the easyJet desk and bought the tickets for one flight. The girl said 'thats a strange name' and he replied, 'Yes, my father is Albanian'. She appeared embarassed for saying it and handed him the tickets. Then he bought tickets from Go from another desk without any questions at all.<br>
<br>
The second incident is new, and I only heard it today. ITN smuggled a toy gun from London Heathrow to Edinburgh, and didn't get stopped at all. Neither of the airports picked the obvious gun shaped object and they smuggled it across in the hand luggage.<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> The point of this discussion is what is happening to our security? Or why has nothing happened to our security in the last year? With the you-know-what coming up why is our airport security so bad?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--><br>
<br>
Of course, this is part of ITN's recent campaign to show up the airports, after they screened the re-inactment of Flight 93 (crashed down in Pennslyvania) and showed the phone calls and the things the terrorists did once they took over the plane etc.<br>
<br>
Well, I might as well mention that there was another bomb scare at Belfast Int. Airport today. This happens every few weeks. It's normally a Tuesday, Thursday or Friday they do it on. A quick phone call saying there is a bomb in the car park will disrupt the flights for a few hours. It also keeps the police very busy I assume. Belfast Int. Airport has always had them of course, just to disrupt the traffic as much as they can, yet they deal firmly with security. You used to go through huge security checkpoints before you got without miles of the airport, with sniffer dogs and car searches...<br>
